parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery acid leak can cause corrosion to various components, including the swingarm, shock, chain, and frame, leading to safety issues and potential accidents.

acid corrosion on swingarm
shock
chain
and frame
white foam-like substance on the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of 2nd Gear and Shift Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of 2nd gear and shift components can cause the gear to slip, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Second gear slips or hesitates
difficulty shifting into second gear
unusual noises or vibrations when shifting into second gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to a loss of control, especially when merging or climbing hills, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
especially when accelerating
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine RPMs surge or fluctuate
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery acid leak can cause corrosion and damage to surrounding components, leading to electrical system failures, which can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Battery acid leakage
corrosion or damage to surrounding components
electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, premature wear, and potentially catastrophic failures.
symptoms: The cooling fan does not operate
the engine overheats
especially in traffic or during prolonged idling
the temperature gauge rises into the red zone
the vehicle loses power or stalls.
